Class Heap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

java.lang.Object
  structures.tree.Heap<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Type of data stored in the heap, must implement method compareTo of generic Comparable interface, to compare priorities.
public class Heap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object

This class implements a generic max heap.

next

public T next()
Sets the cursor to the next position, and returns the item in this heap at that position.
To iterate over this heap, there must be a call to first( ), followed by successive calls to next( ). Iteration is in level-order sequence.

Returns:
Next item in this heap. Null if heap is empty, or cursor is at the end of the heap at the time this method is called, i.e. end of heap was reached.
